</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/20/01 10:19:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1>  When my Guild has reached a point to take down the other dragons, I may need to call on others through the CoG to attend. I see now that the CoG will become a useful tool once I bring my own guild back together, then again I may just scrap it and join a well established guild/aliance in a fit of lazyness. Time will tell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>King and Queen of Lag</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/20/01 11:30:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> All the other dragons would be far past our reaching ability right now unfortunately in my belief. For example Trakanon - some guilds only go in to kill him with people 55+, no lower and they insist that everyones poison resist is a minimum 150 unbuffed. Even with all that they fail, surprising eh? plus you also need the Seb key to get in there which makes things much harder too. I understand that Gore and Sev are not as hard as Trak but still harder than Vox or Naggy. The problem with them is people's faction. I am liked by both of them and I cant honestly see myself wanting to kill either of them. Other than them there are a few others around but they are all difficult to kill by the major ubers so they are kinda way out of our range. At some point we may be ready to go after them but I dont have alot of time between the other dragons so someone else would have to take them over.<br>
<br>
Hope that answers a bit<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho -Fellowship of Faydark-<br>
lvl 51 Elementalist Officer  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/20/01 3:03:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> Oh why must we bards destroy our dragon faction to get our epics. I must admit that I know nothing about Trakanon. From what Lag has said it's enticing to think about. I believe that Trak is within the CoG's reach. it's just a matter of getting together enough people. That's what the CoG is about. I'll comunicate to a few channels I have and see if I can convice them of the feasablity of this, however as I'm staying below 50 for now I might not be successful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>King and Queen of Lag</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/20/01 6:17:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> The only other thing holding us back right now is that KGC just voted on a step ladder system to dragons. In order to climb the ladder you must be able to kill the dragon below it and must be in its rotation. I dont know if its been implemented yet but thats what the majority vote was.<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho -Fellowship of Faydark-<br>
lvl 51 Elementalist Officer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/01 1:08:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1>  Well I can't escape it now. I'm fully entrigued by the politics that exists on this server. Being the tick that I am I wish to suck a little blood of the KGC. Please direct me to their website. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukatellin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katellin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/01 7:45:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> Yes it has been implemented. It only refers to outside Kunark dragons. The steps are.. sev &gt; tal &gt; gore. You have to take down the one before entering rotation on the next. Trak is easier than gore i think. But i think all of them encludeing trak are out of CoG's range myself. I dont think CoG has enough members with good enough gear and sufficiant enough levels and the amount of experience to take these on yet, just my opinion though... You also need to understand what KGC is. Yes it is politics, its all politics, it is where the whole sever communicates and works together to try to come up with a system on certain things so there isnt as much competeing and guilds at each others throats and such stuff like as a server that is all FFA. <p>Katellin Majere 53rd Human Wizard - Muji 55th Human Monk - Fellowship of Faydark</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/01 9:22:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> The Kunark dragons are out of the CoG's reach. If you are level 52, you'll probably be feared most of the time. If you are 55+, you may resist the fear, even with a high magic resist. I don't think that the CoG currently has or will have in the future the means to take down any of the outdoor dragons. These things are COMPLETELY random spawns, between something like 2-5 or maybe 8 days. In order to kill them, you have to be ready to do so on a moment's notice, and do so within a few hours of spawning. I don't see the CoG ever being able to have that much communication among as many people as would be needed. <br>
<br>
Trakanon could be done, but is still problematic in the levels needed. <br>
<br>
If you'll read the FAQ on the Planes and Dragons, you'll see the link to the KGC site, where you would need to gain information about this body. Chances are, if you aren't a guild officer or leader, you won't be able to get in without your leader vouching for you in the public board. <br>
<br>
The FAQ link is on the front page of the CoG web site, at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://members.fortunecity.com/haemish">members.fortunecity.com/haemish</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/01 9:58:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1>  Ahh thank you Haemish. I think I missed that link. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Least Equipped 55th Level Druid</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/01 10:11:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interlog.com/~wings/jane/a_lindgren/lindgren_pics/pippi.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Other dragons</span><hr size=1> Hey Sinian, whatever discussions ensue on the KGC about their policies, any chance you can post it here, too? Lowly me doesn't have access to that board anymore, but I would enjoy reading them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   or e-mail it to me if it's prohibited to cut &amp; paste<br>
<br>
